VALUES
(44, 13, 1, 44, 4, 36, 36, 'Barnabas', 'Connection of Barnabas in Acts', 'This connection highlights the mention of Barnabas in both passages, establishing his role in the early church. Acts 13:1 identifies Barnabas as a prophet and teacher, while Acts 4:36 introduces him as a Levite and ''son of consolation.''', 'keyword', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 1, 44, 15, 35, 35, 'Barnabas', 'Continuity of Ministry in Antioch', 'This connection highlights the ongoing role of Barnabas in the church at Antioch. Both passages emphasize teaching and preaching the word of the Lord.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 1, 48, 2, 9, 9, 'Barnabas', 'Connection of Barnabas in Ministry', 'This connection highlights Barnabas''s role in both passages as a key figure in the early church. In Acts, he is mentioned among the prophets and teachers, while in Galatians, he is recognized as a partner in ministry with Paul.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 1, 42, 3, 1, 1, 'Herod the tetrarch', 'Leadership in Early Church and Governance', 'Both passages emphasize the role of Herod in governance. In Acts, Herod is mentioned in relation to Manaen, indicating a connection between political and religious leadership. This connection highlights the interplay between secular and spiritual authority.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 1, 46, 14, 24, 25, 'certain prophets and teachers', 'Connection of Prophecy and Worship', 'This connection highlights the role of prophets in the church and the impact of their messages on believers and non-believers. Both passages emphasize how prophecy leads to the revelation of God''s truth, prompting worship.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 1, 49, 4, 11, 11, 'prophets and teachers', 'Roles in the Church', 'Both passages emphasize the roles of prophets and teachers within the church. Acts 13:1 lists specific individuals fulfilling these roles, while Ephesians 4:11 categorizes them as gifts given to the church.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 1, 40, 14, 1, 10, 'brought up with Herod the tetrarch', 'Connection between Herod and John', 'Both passages emphasize the figure of Herod, highlighting his role in the imprisonment and execution of John the Baptist. Additionally, the mention of Manaen, who was brought up with Herod, connects the early church in Antioch to the political dynamics surrounding Herod''s actions.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 2, 48, 1, 15, 15, 'Separate me Barnabas and Saul', 'Separation and Calling Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of separation for a divine purpose. Acts 13:2 speaks of God separating Barnabas and Saul for a specific work, while Galatians 1:15 highlights God''s separation of Paul from birth for His grace.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 2, 44, 9, 15, 15, 'for the work whereunto I have called them', 'Connection of Divine Calling', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being chosen for a specific work by God. Acts 13:2 mentions the Holy Ghost calling Barnabas and Saul, while Acts 9:15 describes Saul as a chosen vessel for God''s purpose.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 2, 46, 12, 11, 11, 'the Holy Ghost said, Separate me', 'Work of the Holy Spirit', 'This connection highlights the role of the Holy Spirit in guiding and empowering individuals for specific tasks. Both passages emphasize the Spirit''s active involvement in the selection and distribution of gifts and callings.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 2, 45, 1, 1, 1, 'Separate me Barnabas and Saul', 'Separation for Divine Purpose', 'This connection highlights the theme of being ''separated'' for a specific divine calling. In Acts, Barnabas and Saul are set apart for a work, while in Romans, Paul identifies himself as ''separated unto the gospel of God.''', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 2, 55, 1, 11, 11, 'for the work whereunto I have called them', 'Connection of Apostolic Calling', 'This connection highlights the calling of Barnabas and Saul in Acts 13:2, which parallels Paul''s appointment as a preacher and apostle in 2 Timothy 1:11. Both passages emphasize the divine selection for ministry work.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 2, 27, 9, 3, 3, 'fasted', 'Fasting and Seeking God', 'Both passages emphasize the act of fasting as a means of seeking God''s guidance. In Acts, fasting precedes the Holy Spirit''s direction, while in Daniel, fasting accompanies prayer and supplication to the Lord.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 2, 44, 14, 26, 26, 'for the work whereunto I have called them', 'Commissioning of Barnabas and Saul', 'This connection highlights the commissioning of Barnabas and Saul for their mission. Both passages emphasize the work they were called to fulfill, linking their initial separation to their eventual return.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 3, 44, 6, 6, 6, 'laid their hands on them', 'Connection of Laying on Hands', 'Both passages emphasize the act of laying hands on individuals after prayer. This connection highlights a communal practice of commissioning and blessing within the early church.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 3, 55, 2, 2, 2, 'sent them away', 'Connection of Teaching and Sending', 'This connection highlights the theme of commissioning and teaching. In Acts, the laying on of hands signifies sending individuals for ministry, while in 2 Timothy, the emphasis is on committing teachings to others for further instruction.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 3, 44, 13, 2, 2, 'fasted', 'Connection of Fasting and Sending', 'Both passages emphasize the act of fasting as a precursor to divine calling and action. In Acts 13:2, fasting leads to the Holy Spirit''s instruction, while Acts 13:3 shows the response to that instruction through sending.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 3, 54, 4, 14, 14, NULL, 'Connection of Laying on Hands', 'Both passages emphasize the act of laying on of hands as a significant ritual in the commissioning and recognition of spiritual gifts. Acts 13:3 describes this act in the context of sending out missionaries, while 1 Timothy 4:14 refers to it as a means of imparting a spiritual gift.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 3, 4, 27, 23, 23, NULL, 'Connection of Laying on Hands', 'Both passages emphasize the act of laying hands as a means of commissioning or imparting authority. In Acts, this act follows prayer and fasting, while in Numbers, it is a direct command from the Lord through Moses.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 3, 45, 10, 15, 15, 'sent them away', 'Sending and Preaching Connection', 'This connection highlights the act of sending as essential for preaching. Acts 13:3 describes the sending of missionaries after prayer and fasting, while Romans 10:15 emphasizes the necessity of being sent to preach the gospel.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 3, 54, 5, 22, 22, 'laid their hands on them', 'Connection of Laying on Hands', 'Both passages emphasize the act of laying hands, highlighting its significance in ministry and the caution required in doing so. Acts 13:3 shows the sending forth of individuals through this act, while 1 Timothy 5:22 warns against hastiness in laying hands, suggesting a need for discernment.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 4, 44, 4, 36, 36, 'Cyprus', 'Connection through Barnabas and Cyprus', 'This connection highlights the relationship between Barnabas, a Levite from Cyprus, and the missionary journey to Cyprus initiated by the Holy Ghost. Both passages emphasize Cyprus as a significant location in the early church.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 4, 44, 13, 2, 2, 'by the Holy Ghost', 'Calling and Sending of Apostles', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the Holy Ghost in calling and sending Barnabas and Saul for their mission. Acts 13:2 describes the Holy Ghost''s directive, while Acts 13:4 shows their departure in obedience to that call.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 4, 44, 11, 19, 19, 'Cyprus', 'Connection of Mission to Cyprus', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of Cyprus in the early Christian mission. Acts 11:19 mentions Cyprus as a location where believers preached, while Acts 13:4 describes Paul and Barnabas sailing to Cyprus as part of their missionary journey.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 4, 44, 20, 23, 23, 'by the Holy Ghost', 'Connection of the Holy Ghost', 'This connection highlights the role of the Holy Ghost in guiding and warning. In Acts 13:4, the Holy Ghost sends forth the apostles, while in Acts 20:23, the Holy Ghost warns of future afflictions.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 4, 44, 27, 4, 4, 'sailed to Cyprus', 'Sailing Under Cyprus Connection', 'Both passages emphasize sailing to or under Cyprus, highlighting the geographical significance of Cyprus in the journeys of Paul. This connection illustrates the continuity of travel in the narrative of Acts.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 5, 44, 13, 14, 14, 'synagogues of the Jews', 'Preaching in Synagogues', 'Both passages emphasize the act of preaching in synagogues. In Acts 13:5, the apostles preach in the synagogues of the Jews, while in Acts 13:14, they enter a synagogue in Antioch to continue their ministry.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 5, 44, 13, 46, 46, 'the word of God', 'Preaching to the Jews and Gentiles', 'Both passages emphasize the preaching of the word of God, first to the Jews and then to the Gentiles. This connection highlights the transition in the mission of Paul and Barnabas as they respond to the rejection of their message.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 5, 51, 4, 10, 10, 'John to their minister', 'Connection through Barnabas and John', 'Both passages emphasize the role of John, who is mentioned as a minister in Acts and is identified as Marcus, Barnabas''s sister''s son, in Colossians. This connection highlights the relationships among early Christian workers.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 5, 55, 4, 11, 11, 'minister', 'Ministry and Service Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the role of individuals in ministry. In Acts, John is described as a minister, while in 2 Timothy, Mark is noted as profitable for the ministry.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 5, 11, 19, 21, 21, 'minister', 'Ministry and Service Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the role of a minister serving alongside a leader. In Acts, John is described as a minister, while in 1 Kings, the individual ministers to Elijah after a significant act of commitment.', 'theme', 0.293, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 5, 40, 20, 26, 26, 'minister', 'Ministry and Service in Context', 'This connection highlights the concept of ministry in both passages. Acts 13:5 mentions John as a minister, while Matthew 20:26 emphasizes the role of a minister in achieving greatness.', 'theme', 0.286, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 5, 2, 24, 13, 13, 'minister', 'Ministry and Leadership Connection', 'This connection highlights the role of a minister in both passages. In Acts, John serves as a minister, paralleling Joshua''s role as Moses'' minister in Exodus.', 'theme', 0.27899999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 6, 40, 7, 15, 15, 'false prophet', 'False Prophets and Deception', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of false prophets who deceive others. Acts 13:6 introduces Bar-jesus as a false prophet, while Matthew 7:15 warns to beware of such individuals disguised as harmless.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 6, 62, 4, 1, 1, 'false prophet', 'Connection of False Prophets', 'This connection highlights the presence of false prophets in both passages. Acts 13:6 introduces Bar-jesus as a false prophet, while 1 John 4:1 warns believers to test spirits because many false prophets are in the world.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 6, 47, 11, 13, 13, 'false prophet', 'Connection of False Prophets', 'This connection highlights the theme of false prophets in both passages. Acts 13:6 mentions a ''false prophet,'' while 2 Corinthians 11:13 refers to ''false apostles,'' emphasizing the presence of deceitful figures in the early church.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 6, 2, 22, 18, 18, 'sorcerer', 'Connection Between Sorcery and Witchcraft', 'This connection highlights the condemnation of sorcery and witchcraft in both passages. Acts 13:6 mentions a sorcerer, while Exodus 22:18 explicitly states not to suffer a witch to live.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 6, 5, 13, 1, 3, 'false prophet', 'Connection Between Sorcery and False Prophets', 'This connection highlights the theme of false prophets. Both passages address individuals who lead others away from true worship, emphasizing the danger of following such figures.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 6, 24, 23, 14, 15, 'false prophet', 'Connection of False Prophets', 'This connection highlights the presence of false prophets in both passages. Acts 13:6 mentions a sorcerer and false prophet, paralleling Jeremiah 23:14-15''s condemnation of prophets who lead others into wickedness.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 6, 26, 13, 10, 16, 'false prophet', 'False Prophets and Deception', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of false prophets misleading people. In Acts, Bar-jesus is identified as a false prophet, while Ezekiel condemns prophets who claim peace when there is none. This connection highlights the consequences of such deception.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 7, 44, 13, 12, 12, 'desired to hear the word of God', 'Deputy''s Response to the Word', 'This connection highlights the progression of Sergius Paulus''s journey from desire to hear the word of God to his eventual belief after witnessing a miracle. Both passages emphasize the deputy''s engagement with the teachings of the Lord, culminating in his astonishment and faith.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 7, 44, 19, 38, 38, 'deputy of the country', 'Connection of Legal Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the role of deputies in governance. In Acts 13:7, Sergius Paulus is identified as a deputy, while Acts 19:38 mentions deputies in the context of legal matters. This connection highlights the significance of authority figures in both scenarios.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 7, 20, 18, 15, 15, 'prudent man', 'Prudence and Knowledge Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of prudence in both passages. Sergius Paulus is described as a ''prudent man'' who seeks knowledge, paralleling how ''the heart of the prudent getteth knowledge'' in Proverbs.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 7, 20, 14, 8, 8, 'prudent man', 'Wisdom of the Prudent', 'This connection highlights the theme of prudence in both passages. Sergius Paulus is described as a ''prudent man'' seeking wisdom, while Proverbs emphasizes that ''the wisdom of the prudent'' leads to understanding.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 7, 28, 14, 9, 9, NULL, 'Wisdom and Prudence Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of wisdom and prudence in both passages. Sergius Paulus is described as a ''prudent man'' seeking the word of God, while Hosea emphasizes the importance of being ''prudent'' to understand the ways of the Lord.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 7, 52, 5, 21, 21, 'desired to hear the word of God', 'Seeking Truth and Goodness', 'This connection highlights the desire to discern and embrace truth. In Acts, Sergius Paulus seeks to hear the word of God, while in 1 Thessalonians, believers are encouraged to ''prove all things'' and hold onto what is good.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 8, 55, 3, 8, 8, 'withstood them', 'Resistance to Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the act of resisting faith. Elymas the sorcerer and Jannes and Jambres are depicted as figures who oppose the truth and seek to turn others away from belief.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 8, 44, 13, 6, 7, 'sorcerer', 'Connection of Sorcery and Opposition', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of a sorcerer, Elymas, who seeks to oppose the faith of the deputy, Sergius Paulus. This connection highlights the conflict between faith and sorcery in the narrative.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 8, 55, 4, 14, 15, 'withstood them', 'Opposition to the Faith', 'Both passages emphasize individuals who withstood the faith and opposed the apostles'' message. Elymas the sorcerer and Alexander the coppersmith are depicted as adversaries, actively seeking to undermine the spread of the Gospel.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 8, 44, 9, 36, 36, NULL, 'Contrast of Faith and Works', 'This connection highlights the contrast between Elymas, who seeks to turn others away from faith, and Tabitha, who is described as full of good works. Both passages emphasize the impact of individual actions on the faith of others.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 8, 2, 7, 11, 13, 'sorcerer', 'Connection of Sorcery and Opposition', 'This connection highlights the theme of sorcery and opposition to faith. Both Elymas and the Egyptian magicians represent forces that seek to undermine belief in God’s power.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 8, 11, 22, 24, 24, 'seeking to turn away the deputy', 'Opposition to Prophetic Voices', 'This connection highlights the theme of opposition faced by prophets. Elymas seeks to turn away the deputy from the faith, similar to Zedekiah''s physical confrontation with Micaiah, both representing resistance to divine messages.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 8, 24, 28, 1, 1, 'turn away the deputy from the faith', 'Opposition to Prophetic Voices', 'This connection highlights the theme of opposition to prophetic figures. In both passages, individuals seek to turn others away from faith or truth, illustrating a common struggle against divine messages.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 9, 33, 3, 8, 8, 'filled with the Holy Ghost', 'Connection of Spirit Empowerment', 'This connection highlights the theme of being filled with the Spirit for the purpose of declaring truth. Both passages emphasize the empowerment of individuals by the Spirit of the Lord to confront sin and transgression.', 'theme', 0.46799999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 9, 44, 4, 8, 8, 'filled with the Holy Ghost', 'Filled with the Holy Ghost', 'Both passages emphasize individuals being ''filled with the Holy Ghost'' as they address others. This connection highlights the empowerment by the Holy Spirit in their respective ministries.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 9, 44, 2, 4, 4, 'filled with the Holy Ghost', 'Connection of Holy Spirit Filling', 'Both passages emphasize being filled with the Holy Ghost, highlighting the transformative power of the Spirit in believers. This connection illustrates a continuity in the experience of empowerment by the Holy Spirit in the early church.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 9, 41, 3, 5, 5, NULL, 'Healing and Divine Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the act of restoration through divine intervention. In Acts, Paul, filled with the Holy Ghost, demonstrates authority, while in Mark, Jesus restores the man''s hand, showcasing His power over physical ailments.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 9, 42, 20, 17, 17, NULL, 'Connection of Rejection and Authority', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine authority in both passages. Saul, filled with the Holy Ghost, represents a new foundation in faith, paralleling the rejected stone becoming the cornerstone in Luke.', 'theme', 0.3, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 10, 43, 8, 44, 44, 'child of the devil', 'Connection of Deception and Evil', 'Both passages emphasize the nature of the devil as a deceiver and an enemy of righteousness. Acts 13:10 describes the individual as ''child of the devil'' and ''enemy of all righteousness,'' paralleling John 8:44''s depiction of the devil as a liar and murderer.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 10, 40, 13, 38, 38, 'child of the devil', 'Children of the Wicked One', 'Both passages emphasize the distinction between the children of righteousness and the children of the wicked. Acts 13:10 refers to a ''child of the devil,'' while Matthew 13:38 identifies ''the children of the wicked one,'' highlighting the conflict between good and evil.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 10, 47, 11, 3, 3, 'all subtilty', 'Subtlety and Deception Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of subtilty and deception in both passages. In Acts, the speaker addresses a deceiver, while in 2 Corinthians, Paul warns against being corrupted by similar cunning.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 10, 28, 14, 9, 9, 'the right ways of the Lord', 'Righteousness and the Ways of the Lord', 'This connection highlights the theme of righteousness and the right ways of the Lord. Both passages emphasize the contrast between the just who walk in the right ways and those who pervert them.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 10, 48, 1, 7, 7, 'pervert the right ways of the Lord', 'Perverting the Gospel', 'Both passages emphasize the act of perverting the right ways of the Lord and the gospel of Christ. They highlight the presence of deceitful individuals who disrupt the truth of God''s message.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 10, 42, 11, 52, 52, 'pervert the right ways of the Lord', 'Opposition to Righteousness', 'Both passages emphasize the hindrance of righteousness and knowledge. In Acts, the speaker condemns the perversion of the Lord''s ways, while in Luke, the lawyers are criticized for blocking access to knowledge.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 10, 62, 3, 8, 8, 'child of the devil', 'Connection of Sin and the Devil', 'This connection highlights the portrayal of the devil as the source of sin and mischief. Both passages emphasize the opposition to righteousness and the destructive nature of the devil''s works.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 11, 2, 9, 3, 3, 'the hand of the Lord is upon', 'Divine Hand and Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize the ''hand of the Lord'' as a sign of divine intervention leading to judgment. In Acts, it results in blindness, while in Exodus, it brings a grievous murrain upon livestock.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 11, 19, 32, 4, 4, 'the hand of the Lord is upon thee', 'Divine Hand and Consequences', 'This connection highlights the theme of the ''hand of the Lord'' causing physical and spiritual consequences. In both passages, the heavy hand signifies divine intervention leading to a state of distress or blindness.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 11, 9, 5, 11, 11, 'the hand of the Lord is upon thee', 'Divine Hand and Consequences', 'This connection highlights the theme of the ''hand of God'' bringing severe consequences. In both passages, the hand of God results in physical affliction and fear among people, illustrating divine intervention.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 11, 58, 10, 31, 31, 'the hand of the Lord is upon thee', 'Fear of God''s Judgment', 'This connection highlights the consequences of falling into the hands of God, as seen in both passages. Acts 13:11 illustrates a physical manifestation of divine judgment through blindness, while Hebrews 10:31 emphasizes the fear associated with encountering God''s power.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 11, 18, 19, 21, 21, 'the hand of the Lord is upon thee', 'Divine Hand and Human Suffering', 'This connection highlights the theme of the ''hand of God'' affecting individuals. In both passages, the ''hand'' signifies divine intervention, resulting in physical and emotional turmoil.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 11, 43, 9, 39, 39, 'not seeing the sun for a season', 'Blindness and Spiritual Insight', 'This connection highlights the theme of blindness as a metaphor for spiritual insight. In Acts, physical blindness is imposed, while in John, spiritual blindness is addressed, suggesting a deeper understanding of sight and insight.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 11, 61, 2, 17, 17, NULL, 'Connection of Darkness and Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of darkness as a form of judgment. In Acts, the mist and darkness signify immediate consequence, while in 2 Peter, the mist of darkness represents eternal judgment.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 12, 47, 10, 4, 5, 'the doctrine of the Lord', 'Belief and Knowledge of God', 'This connection highlights the theme of belief in God’s power and doctrine. Both passages emphasize the importance of understanding and submitting to the knowledge of God, as seen in the deputy''s astonishment and the call to bring thoughts into obedience.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 12, 44, 13, 7, 7, NULL, 'Deputy Sergius Paulus'' Belief', 'Both passages emphasize the deputy, Sergius Paulus, and his desire to hear the word of God, which leads to his belief after witnessing the miraculous event. This connection highlights the transformation of the deputy from curiosity to faith.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 12, 42, 4, 22, 22, 'astonished at the doctrine of the Lord', 'Wonder and Belief in Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the astonishment and wonder experienced by those who hear the teachings of Jesus. In Acts, the deputy is ''astonished at the doctrine of the Lord,'' while in Luke, the people ''wondered at the gracious words'' of Jesus.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 12, 40, 7, 28, 29, 'astonished at the doctrine', 'Authority and Astonishment in Teaching', 'Both passages emphasize the astonishment of the audience at the doctrine being presented. In Acts, the deputy believes after being astonished at the doctrine of the Lord, while in Matthew, the people are astonished at Jesus'' authoritative teaching.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 12, 40, 27, 54, 54, 'astonished at the doctrine of the Lord', 'Response to Divine Revelation', 'Both passages emphasize a response to divine revelation, with individuals recognizing the truth of God through extraordinary events. The deputy in Acts is astonished at the doctrine of the Lord, while the centurion in Matthew acknowledges Jesus as the Son of God after witnessing miraculous occurrences.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
